Paul Omokuvie, Bauchi Governor Bala Mohammed of Bauchi State has launched the ‘Clean Nigeria- Use the Toilet’ as part of measures to boost  sanitary and hygienic conditions in the state. A statement by Senior Special Assistant on Media to the governor,  Muktar Gidado, said  the  programme was  fagged off, yesterday, at the Eagle Square, Abuja. The flag -off was a national transformation initiative aimed at mobilising the populace to imbibe the culture of safe defecation practice  towards the attainment of the national target of making Nigeria open  defecation free by  2025.